    tool_output=ToolOutput(
        output='# Composition of AI Segment Revenue for FY2025 ($3,201 Million)\n\n## Revenue Disaggregation by Type\n\nBased on the revenue disaggregation table in the filing, the AI segment\'s $3,201 million is composed of two broad categories:\n\n| Revenue Type | FY2025 ($ millions) |\n|---|---|\n| Advertising | $1,844 |\n| AI Solutions & Infrastructure | $1,357 |\n| **Total AI Segment** | **$3,201** |\n\n## Revenue Streams Included in the AI Segment\n\nThe filing describes the AI segment as generating revenue from **the sale of digital platform services, including advertising, subscription, and licensing services** offered to consumers and enterprise customers. Specifically, the segment comprises two principal revenue categories:\n\n### 1. Advertising Revenue ($1,844M)\n- Sale of ad products displayed on the **X platform**\n- Recognized in the period when advertising is delivered, as evidenced by a user engaging with an ad in a manner satisfying the advertiser\'s selected engagement criteria\n- The Company acts as principal for ads sold directly through X (gross recognition) and as agent for ads sold through SSP partners\n\n### 2. AI Solutions & Infrastructure Revenue ($1,357M)\nThis category includes three sub-streams:\n\n- **(i) Premium subscriptions on X and Grok** — recognized ratably over the subscription term (ranging from month-to-month to one year)\n- **(ii) Data licensing arrangements** — generally recognized ratably over the period (from month-to-month to two years) as the customer consumes and benefits from the use of the licensed data\n- **(iii) API access to Grok models** — recognized ratably over the contract term (typically month-to-month or up to one year) for stand-ready access, or as services are consumed for usage-based arrangements\n\n## Does the Filing Disclose Grok Standalone Subscription Revenue Separately?\n\n**No.** The filing does **not** disclose Grok standalone subscription revenue as a separate line item. Throughout the document, Grok subscription revenue is consistently reported **combined with X subscription revenue** as a single figure. Examples from the filing:\n\n- *"The increase in AI solutions and infrastructure revenue is mainly due to an increase in **X and Grok subscription revenue** of $365 million"*\n- *"premium subscriptions on **X and Grok** which is recognized ratably over the period of the subscription term"*\n- *"an increase in **Grok and X subscription revenue** of $177 million"*\n\nThe filing provides no breakout isolating the Grok-only portion of subscription revenue from the X portion.\n\n## Additional Context on FY2025 AI Revenue Growth\n\nThe MD&A explains that the AI segment\'s year-over-year revenue increase of $581 million (22.2%) was driven by:\n\n| Driver | Increase ($ millions) |\n|---|---|\n| X and Grok subscription revenue | +$365 |\n| Data licensing arrangements | +$88 |\n| Advertising revenue | +$116 |\n| Other (residual) | +$12 |\n\nThe filing also notes that in 2023 and 2024, *"substantially all of our AI segment revenue consisted of advertising, subscriptions, and data licensing revenue generated from X, formerly known as Twitter,"* indicating that Grok-related subscription and API revenue became a more meaningful contributor in 2025 as the AI segment expanded beyond its legacy X-based advertising and subscription business.',
