-1 Chunk**\nThe chunk outlining the company\'s monetization strategy details the following:\n*   **AI-Driven Advertising Initiatives:** The company focuses on making ads feel like content by ensuring they are contextually relevant, aligned with user interests, and integrated into real-time conversations. Grok supports this by helping advertisers with campaign creation, creative optimization, and alignment with trending topics and user intent. While ad pricing is affected by the global economy and competition, the company believes continued investment in AI-powered advertising will improve advertiser ROI.\n*   **Conversion to Paid Subscriptions:** The company is focused on converting its user base into paying subscribers through X (Premium and Premium+) and Grok subscription offerings. Subscribers gain enhanced functionality, exclusive features, and access to the latest AI models.\n*   **Subscriber Metrics:** As of March 31, 2026, the company reached approximately 6.3 million active paid subscribers in total. This consisted of roughly 4.4 million X Premium and Premium+ paid subscribers and approximately 1.9 million SuperGrok, SuperGrok Heavy, and SuperGrok Lite paid subscribers.\n*   **Grok\'s Rapid Model Development:** The AI segment has demonstrated exceptional "model velocity," developing leading frontier models at a faster rate of innovation than competitors since launching Grok. The company plans to continue adding features and releasing increasingly capable Grok models to increase the subscriber penetration rate, believing this pace of innovation strengthens the subscription value proposition and supports long-term subscriber growth.',
